title: The New Original Wonder Woman
description: After a dogfight with a Nazi plane, U.S. Air Force Steve Trevor crashlands on an uncharted island in the Bermuda Triangle. Paradise Island is inhabited only by women, and their existence has been kept a secret for thousands of years. Learning of the Nazi threat to humanity, the Amazon princess, Diana, is chosen to accompany Trevor back to the United States to battle the Third Reich. Garbed in a skimpy red, white & blue costume and armed with a magic lasso that forces anyone within its grasp to tell the truth, Diana uses her powers as Wonder Woman to battle the forces of evil.

title: Wonder Woman Meets Baroness Von Gunther
description: Steve is framed for charges of treason by Nazi spies and Wonder Woman finds herself in trouble when she loses her magic lasso while trying to rescue him.

title: Fausta, the Nazi Wonder Woman
description: A Nazi spy travels to America to learn Wonder Woman's secrets. In the process, she poses as a second Wonder Woman and kidnaps Diana.

title: Beauty on Parade
description: Diana goes undercover at a beauty pageant to try to uncover a suspected spy operation behind the facade.

title: The Feminum Mystique: Part 1
description: Wonder Woman's sister Drusilla is sent from Paradise Island to Washington to tell Diana to come home. Drusilla discovers her own alter ego, Wonder Girl, and is kidnapped by the Nazis.

title: The Feminum Mystique: Part 2
description: Drusilla accidentally reveals the location of Paradise Island to the Nazis who want to go there to harvest Feminum. Wonder Woman must return home to protect her people.

title: Wonder Woman vs Gargantua
description: The Nazis try to get back an agent who turned on them. To help them in their efforts, they brainwash a gorilla named Gargantua to hate Wonder Woman.

title: The Pluto File
description: An American scientist figures out how to make man-made earthquakes.

title: Last of the $2 Bills
description: Top Nazi agent Wotan has two surgically altered doubles replace the man in charge of the Bureau of Printing and Engraving and his girlfriend, a waitress. The plan is to steal the $2 engraving plates and use them to collapse the American economy.

title: Judgment from Outer Space: Part 1
description: September, 1942. Andros, an observer from a council of alien planets is sent to Earth to pass judgment on the primitive, warlike humans race.

title: Judgment from Outer Space: Part 2
description: Andros has been kidnapped and taken to Germany. When Wonder Woman attempts to rescue him, Andros tells her he sees little difference between the way the Nazis and the Allied Forces wage war. Maj. Steve Trevor mounts a rescue mission of his own together with British agent Mallory.

title: Formula 407
description: A scientist in Argentina creates a formula that makes rubber indestructible.

title: The Bushwhackers
description: Wonder Woman battles cattle rustlers in Texas.

title: Wonder Woman in Hollywood
description: Major Steve Trevor is asked to re-enact a heroic deed for Hollywood.

title: The Return of Wonder Woman
description: Having returned home some time after WW II, Wonder Woman once again must deal with a plane crash landing on Paradise Island. This time, the plane is carrying Steve Trevor's son, and the danger comes from international terrorists. Wonder Woman returns to "man's world", where as Diana Prince - IADC agent, she works with Steve Trevor Jr. to fight more 'modern-day' battles.

title: Anschluss '77
description: Nazis hiding in South America try to rebuild the Third Reich by cloning Hitler.

title: The Man Who Could Move the World
description: Japanese man, bitter over the grief that he believes Wonder Woman caused him in WW II, unleashes his telekinetic powers against her.

title: The Bermuda Triangle Crisis
description: I.A.D.C's Operation Sea Harvest is being compromised by Ray Manta and his I.C.O.P.E. organization. Diana is especially worried since both parties are operating around the Bermuda Triangle, dangerously close to Paradise Island.

title: Knockout
description: Several I.A.D.C. agents are being targeted for kidnapping by a terrorist organization. Diana Prince manages to escape as Wonder Woman, but Stever Trevor is not so lucky. Trying to safeguard a Trade Conference in L.A. and at the same time find Trevor and free him, Diana finds an ally in a Vietnam vet turned cab driver called Pete.

title: The Pied Piper
description: Rock and Roll star, Hamlin Rule hypnotizes his female fans, to rob his concerts for him.

title: The Queen and the Thief
description: Diana and Steve go undercover at the Malakan consulate in Palm Beach to prevent international jewel thief Evan Robley from stealing the Crown jewels of Malakar and catch him.

title: I Do, I Do
description: Diana Prince marries White House aide Christian Harrison with Joe Atkinson giving her away and Steve Trevor acting as the best man. But Diana is really on a mission to find a leak located at a health spa frequented by the wives of White House officials.

title: The Man Who Made Volcanoes
description: Volcanoes are mysteriously appearing all over the world. Diana is assigned to replace the missing IADC agent on the case in Mexico. As Wonder Woman, she also faces two rival teams of Chinese and Russian agents, who are convinced the US is behind the volcanic attacks.

title: Mind Stealers from Outer Space: Part 1
description: Space traveler Andros returns seeking Wonder Woman's help in defending earth from an invasion of the body snatching Scrill.

title: Mind Stealers from Outer Space: Part 2
description: If Wonder Woman and Andros don't find a way to defeat the alien Skrill in 24 hours, the planet Earth will be contaminated by higher forces from outer space.

title: The Deadly Toys
description: Three scientists are replaced by androids one by one after they collectively refuse to create a devastating weapon known as Project XYZ. When Diana Prince investigates a suspicious toy maker she meets face to face with... Wonder Woman.

title: Light-fingered Lady
description: Posing as jewel thief Lil Thaxton, Diana Prince infiltrates Anton Caribe's gang of thieves who are about to embark on his most ambitious robbery. Caribe intends to retire after this one, so it is the IADC's last chance to catch this elusive criminal.

title: Screaming Javelins
description: Megalomaniac Marion Mariposa is putting together a dream team of athletes to represent Mariposalia in the next Olympics. He does this by kidnapping them and threatening their loved ones. Diana Prince fails to protect Russian defector Nadia Samara, but inspires Mariposa to use her as bait to lure Wonder Woman into his clutches.

title: Diana's Disappearing Act
description: Count Cagliostro has found a way to turn lead into gold, albeit temporarily. An example of his work has been sent to Diana Prince in the form of a golden locket. The Count instructs his accomplices to get the locket back before it the fleeting nature of the gold is exposed.

title: Death in Disguise
description: An attempt on Diana Prince's life give her a clue that illusive assassin for hire Woodward Nightingale has a contract out on a target with the initials 'C.R.A.I.' International Industrialist Carlo Amadeo Ricardo Indrezzano appears to be the most likely target, so Diana becomes his bodyguard. And by default, so does Wonder Woman.

title: IRAC Is Missing
description: The world's most powerful computers are being drained of their information by William Havitol who plans to use the information to become ruler of the entire world. I.R.A.C. is next on his wish list and Diana is on the case to stop him with a little help from Rover the roving computer.

title: Flight to Oblivion
description: Diana and Steve are undercover at San Remo Air Force Base to keep an eye on the test flight of the new Z-400. Also there is the rock group 'The Hull City Howlers' and their manager Edmund Dante, who has a way of putting people under a spell to do his bidding.

title: Seance of Terror
description: Several attendees of a World Peace Conference are lured away by a psychic boy who takes Polaroids featuring deceased loved ones. As Diana failed to protect one of the dignitaries, she is taken off the case and told to go on vacation.

title: The Man Who Wouldn't Tell
description: A janitor is pursued by his employer and a rival company after discovering the key ingredient for a new explosive formula.

title: The Girl from Ilandia
description: While out on his yacht, newspaper man Simon Penrose finds a young girl on a raft. She has no I.D. but wears mysterious, difficult to remove jewelry. Simon calls in his old friend Diana Prince, who recognizes the jewels as being from the other dimensional and legendary Islandia. Of course she keeps this information to herself, and confides to the girl as Wonder Woman.

title: The Murderous Missile
description: Wonder Woman saves the world from an angry scientist and a "thinking" missile.

title: My Teenage Idol Is Missing
description: Criminal Mastermind Raleigh Crichton abducts pop idol Lane Kincaid and replaces him with his twin brother Michael. Persistent fan Whitney Sprinfield witnesses the kidnapping. Although her rich and powerful father doesn't believe her, Whitney persuades Diana Prince to investigate.

title: Hot Wheels
description: Diana helps the police find a car theft ring and a Rolls Royce with a valuable microchip hidden in its hood ornament.

title: The Deadly Sting
description: When several sporting events end with less favored team winning, Diana and Steve try to find out if something is going on. At the same time the mob is also worried so tell the man in charge of the sports betting to find out. And they discover a scientist who needs money for his project making people do things that they wouldn't do. When the criminals orders the scientist to tell someone to kill someone he tries to get out.

title: The Fine Art of Crime
description: Wonder Woman foils a ring of art thieves who use realistic-looking statues who are actually people in suspended animation to rob museums.

title: Disco Devil
description: A man lures important government officials into his disco so he can rob their minds. Music legend Wolfman Jack guest stars.

title: Formicida
description: A deadly pesticide threatens the human race and a strange ant woman threatens a billionaire industrialist as the IADC and Wonder Woman find themselves on both sides.

title: Time Bomb
description: Cassandra Loren uses a Time Portal to travel from 2155 back to 1978 and make herself a fortune in a time when that still meant something. Adam Clement, the Time Portal's inventor, follows Cassandra in order to stop her. He is quick to contact the I.A.D.C. (because his grandfather worked for them around the year 2000) and Diana Prince in particular.

title: Skateboard Wiz
description: Diana spends her vacation with friends in California. As Wonder Woman, she uncovers an illegal gambling organization with the help of a young skateboarder who also happens to have a photographic memory.

title: The Deadly Dolphin
description: A land developer kidnaps a trained dolphin and uses it to sink an oil tanker which will lower beachfront property values.

title: Stolen Faces
description: Wonder Woman uncovers a plot to steal millions of dollars in jewels from wealthy party-goers by impersonating her and her colleagues.

title: Pot of Gold
description: A petty crook steals gold in order to buy $100 bill printing plates from a counterfeiter, but Wonder Woman foils the sale.

title: Gault's Brain
description: The living brain of a dead billionaire seeks to have itself transplanted into the perfect physical specimen.

title: Going, Going, Gone
description: Diana tries to prevent a scientist from selling an atomic bomb on the black market.

title: Spaced Out
description: Master thief James Kimball steals tree crystal lenses from the Torrence Aerospace plant but has to hide them in a crate in order to get out clean. The crate's destination is the Space Questicon in the L.A Hotel Le Baron where Sylvester Grogan is setting up a display of Appolo moon rocks. Diana Prince is dispatched to find the stolen lenses and is staying at the same hotel. Kimball attends the convention in disguise to snatch back his loot. Meanwhile his employer, afraid Kimball will offer the lenses to a higher bidder has him shadowed as well.

title: The Starships Are Coming
description: A man vanishes after a UFO sighting and Wonder Woman discovers the aliens may have started their conquest of Earth.

title: Amazon Hot Wax
description: Diana Prince poses as a singer, using the cover identity of "Kathy Meadows," so that, as Wonder Woman, she can crack a record-extortion ring. This installment showcases series lead Lynda Carter's musical talents; one of the two selections she performs, "Toto (Don't It Feel Like Paradise)," is from the album "Portrait," which Ms. Carter released on the Epic Records label in the late 1970s.

title: The Richest Man in the World
description: Wonder Woman stops the black market sale of a super-secret missile guidance systems scrambling device and thus avoids an international incident.

title: A Date with Doomsday
description: Diana uses a computer dating service to investigate a stolen vial containing a deadly virus.

title: The Girl with a Gift for Disaster
description: A young woman with destructive psychokinetic powers unknowingly helps a thieve steal some priceless historical documents.

title: The Boy Who Knew Her Secret: Part 1
description: Diana Prince investigating a strange alien force in a small suburban community, is seen whirling into Wonder Woman by a young boy.

title: The Boy Who Knew Her Secret: Part 2
description: With a boy knowing that she is really Wonder Woman, Diana Prince continues her battle against a mysterious alien invasion.

title: The Man Who Could Not Die
description: Wonder Woman meets the invulnerable man and they join forces to fight crime.

title: Phantom of the Roller Coaster: Part 1
description: The leader of a spy ring must deal with a phantom-like man and Wonder Woman before he can locate his headquarters in an old amusement park. Part one of a two-part episode.

title: Phantom of the Roller Coaster: Part 2
description: Wonder Woman's strength, ability and quick action saves hundreds of people from a disastrous accident at an amusement park. Part two of a two-part episode.
